Wash and dry produce.

Thinly slice @tomato{1} into rounds. Halve @potato bun{2}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%oz} and @fajita spice blend{1%tbsp}.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

Form beef mixture into two equal-size balls (four balls for 4 servings); season all
over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large, preferably nonstick, pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add beef and flatten each ball with a #spatula{} to create very
thin patties. (TIP: Do so carefully; oil may splatter a bit.) Cook to desired
doneness, ~{3-4%minutes} per side. (Don't worry if the patties aren't perfectly
round—those irregular edges will turn crispy.)

In the last ~{1-2%minutes} of cooking, top patties with @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}
and cover pan to melt cheese.

While patties cook, toast buns until golden brown.

Spread top buns with @guacamole{4%tbsp} and @hot sauce{1%tsp} to taste. Place
patties, tomato, and a few @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%oz}(crushed) on bottom
buns. Close buns.

Divide burgers between plates. Serve with remaining tortilla chips on the side.